@startuml
title E6-01 — Propose and Approve Debt Transaction\nTransaction Information Evolution

top to bottom direction

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam nodesep 80
skinparam ranksep 90
skinparam padding 18

skinparam rectangle {
  FontSize 14
  MinimumWidth 230
}

rectangle "Draft Transaction\n\nInitial business terms captured" as Draft

rectangle "Validated Transaction\n\nCompleteness and business rules confirmed" as Validated

rectangle "Submitted Version\n\nTerms locked for approval review" as Submitted

rectangle "APPROVAL DECISION\n\nApprove or return?" as Decision

rectangle "Returned Transaction\n\nReason and required changes recorded" as Returned

rectangle "Revised Version\n\nCorrections captured as a new version" as Revised

rectangle "Approved Transaction\n\nAuthorized terms become official" as Approved

rectangle "Ready for\nSecurity Preparation" as Ready

Draft --> Validated : Validate
Validated --> Submitted : Submit
Submitted --> Decision : Review

Decision --> Approved : Approve
Decision --> Returned : Return

Returned --> Revised : Correct
Revised --> Validated : Revalidate

Approved --> Ready : Release

note right of Draft
Core information includes:

- Product type
- Principal amount
- Coupon or spread
- Trade date
- Settlement date
- Maturity date
end note

note right of Submitted
The submitted version is
preserved and cannot be
silently changed during review.
end note

note right of Approved
The approved version includes:

- Final transaction terms
- Approver identity
- Decision timestamp
- Complete audit history
end note

legend bottom
|= Information stage |= Meaning |
| Draft | Proposed terms may still be edited |
| Validated | Required data and rules have passed |
| Submitted | A controlled version is awaiting approval |
| Returned | Corrections are required and explained |
| Approved | The authorized version becomes the official record |
endlegend

@enduml